        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/26/1/49/1",
        "text": [
          " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ ع يَقُولُ اَلشِّتَاءُ رَبِيعُ اَلْمُؤْمِنِ يَطُولُ فِيهِ لَيْلُهُ فَيَسْتَعِينُ بِهِ عَلَى قِيَامِهِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.badr-shahin": [
            "Mohammad bin Ali Majilwayh, Allah may have mercy upon him, narrated to us from… Mohammed bin Sulaiman ad-Dailami that Abu Abdullah (a) said: Winter is the believer’s spring. Its long nights help the believer offer his rites of worship."
